  {"@type":"Question","name":"What are the best alternatives to the ecom Tab-Ex?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The top alternatives are: i.safe MOBILE IS930.1 (compact 8-inch Android, ~€2,400), Aegex 10 IS (Windows Zone 1, ~€4,500), ecom Tab-Ex Pro DZ2 (premium Android with AMOLED, ~€3,800), Getac F110-Ex (large Windows Zone 2, ~€3,800), and Zebra XPAD L10 IS (enterprise Android/Windows Zone 2, ~€3,500). All are ATEX certified for hazardous areas."}},
  {"@type":"Question","name":"Is the ecom Tab-Ex the best ATEX tablet?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The Tab-Ex 03 DZ2 is the most popular ATEX Zone 1 Android tablet and the right choice for most deployments. However, it is not the best for every use case: the i.safe IS930.1 is better for one-hand portability, the Aegex 10 is better for Windows applications, and the Getac F110-Ex offers a larger display for Zone 2 environments."}},
