<main class="max-w-[900px] mx-auto px-6 pt-12 pb-20">
  <article>
    <nav class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs mb-6" style="color:var(--ash)">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-[color:var(--ink)]">Home</a>
      <i class="ph ph-caret-right"></i>
      <a href="/best-atex-tablets-2026.html" class="hover:text-[color:var(--ink)]">Best 2026</a>
      <i class="ph ph-caret-right"></i>
      <span style="color:var(--graphite)">Tab-Ex Alternatives</span>
    </nav>

    <div class="mb-10">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest mb-3" style="color:var(--ash)">Alternatives &middot; July 2026</p>
      <h1 class="serif text-[clamp(2rem,4vw,3rem)] leading-[1.1] mb-4">
        ecom Tab-Ex Alternatives
      </h1>
      <p class="text-[17px] leading-relaxed max-w-[640px]" style="color:var(--graphite)">
        The ecom Tab-Ex 03 DZ2 is the most widely deployed ATEX Zone 1 Android tablet &mdash; but it is not the only option. Whether you need a different OS, a smaller form factor, a lower price, or Zone 2 certification, here are 5 certified alternatives worth evaluating.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Reference: what you're comparing against -->
    <div class="card mb-10" style="border-left:4px solid var(--accent)">
      <h2 class="text-[15px] font-semibold mb-2" style="color:var(--accent)">The benchmark: ecom Tab-Ex 03 DZ2</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-4 text-[13px]" style="color:var(--graphite)">
        <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">Zone</strong><br/>Zone 1 / 21</div>
        <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">OS</strong><br/>Android 13</div>
        <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">Display</strong><br/>10.1&Prime; TFT</div>
        <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">Price</strong><br/>~&euro;3,200</div>
        <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">Gas Group</strong><br/>IIC</div>
        <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">Weight</strong><br/>~690 g</div>
        <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">IP</strong><br/>IP68</div>
        <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">MDM</strong><br/>Samsung Knox</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Alternatives list -->
    <section class="space-y-6 mb-12">

      <!-- Alternative 1: i.safe IS930.1 -->
      <div class="alt-card">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-start justify-between gap-3 mb-3">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-[18px] font-semibold">1. i.safe MOBILE IS930.1</h3>
            <p class="text-[13px]" style="color:var(--ash)">Best for: compact one-hand use &amp; lower budget</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1">
            <span class="badge badge-z1">Zone 1</span>
            <span class="badge badge-android">Android</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-3 text-[13px] mb-4" style="color:var(--graphite)">
          <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">Display</strong><br/>8.0&Prime; IPS</div>
          <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">Weight</strong><br/>~570 g</div>
          <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">Price</strong><br/>~&euro;2,400</div>
          <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">IP</strong><br/>IP68</div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-[14px] leading-relaxed mb-3" style="color:var(--graphite)">
          The most direct alternative for teams that want a Zone 1 Android tablet but need a smaller, lighter device. At 570g and 8 inches, the IS930.1 is holdable in one hand &mdash; ideal for confined spaces, ladder climbs, and mobile inspection routes. Saves ~&euro;800 per unit versus the Tab-Ex 03.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[14px] leading-relaxed mb-3" style="color:var(--graphite)">
          <strong style="color:var(--ink)">Trade-off:</strong> Smaller screen makes drawing review and SCADA dashboards less practical. Uses standard Android Enterprise instead of Samsung Knox, so less deep MDM integration. Runs Android 12 (one version behind the Tab-Ex 03).
        </p>
        <a href="/ecom-tab-ex-03-vs-isafe-is930.html" style="color:var(--accent)" class="text-[13px] hover:underline">Full comparison: Tab-Ex 03 vs IS930.1 &rarr;</a>
      </div>

      <!-- Alternative 2: ecom Tab-Ex Pro DZ2 -->
      <div class="alt-card">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-start justify-between gap-3 mb-3">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-[18px] font-semibold">2. ecom Tab-Ex Pro DZ2</h3>
            <p class="text-[13px]" style="color:var(--ash)">Best for: premium display &amp; S-Pen workflows</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1">
            <span class="badge badge-z1">Zone 1</span>
            <span class="badge badge-android">Android</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-3 text-[13px] mb-4" style="color:var(--graphite)">
          <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">Display</strong><br/>10.1&Prime; AMOLED</div>
          <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">Weight</strong><br/>~750 g</div>
          <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">Price</strong><br/>~&euro;3,800</div>
          <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">IP</strong><br/>IP68</div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-[14px] leading-relaxed mb-3" style="color:var(--graphite)">
          Not a competitor but an upgrade within ecom&rsquo;s own lineup. The Pro adds a vibrant AMOLED display (better outdoors and in bright process areas) and S-Pen support for field annotations, mark-ups on P&amp;ID drawings, and signature capture. Same Samsung Knox ecosystem, same certification.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[14px] leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--graphite)">
          <strong style="color:var(--ink)">Trade-off:</strong> ~&euro;600 more per unit and 60g heavier than the standard Tab-Ex 03. The AMOLED display is a genuine advantage, but only worth the premium if your workflows benefit from stylus input or outdoor readability.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Alternative 3: Aegex 10 IS -->
      <div class="alt-card">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-start justify-between gap-3 mb-3">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-[18px] font-semibold">3. Aegex 10 IS</h3>
            <p class="text-[13px]" style="color:var(--ash)">Best for: Windows desktop applications in Zone 1</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1">
            <span class="badge badge-z1">Zone 1</span>
            <span class="badge badge-win">Windows</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-3 text-[13px] mb-4" style="color:var(--graphite)">
          <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">Display</strong><br/>10.1&Prime; IPS</div>
          <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">Weight</strong><br/>~850 g</div>
          <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">Price</strong><br/>~&euro;4,500</div>
          <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">IP</strong><br/>IP65</div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-[14px] leading-relaxed mb-3" style="color:var(--graphite)">
          The only Windows Zone 1 tablet on the market. If your field engineers need to run SAP GUI, SCADA HMI clients, PI ProcessBook, or custom .NET applications, the Aegex 10 is the only certified option that does not require application re-platforming.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[14px] leading-relaxed mb-3" style="color:var(--graphite)">
          <strong style="color:var(--ink)">Trade-off:</strong> 40% more expensive, 23% heavier, and IP65 (not submersible). Windows also means larger attack surface and slower boot times compared to Android. Not ideal for simple inspection/camera workflows where Android is faster and lighter.
        </p>
        <a href="/ecom-tab-ex-vs-aegex-10.html" style="color:var(--accent)" class="text-[13px] hover:underline">Full comparison: Tab-Ex 03 vs Aegex 10 &rarr;</a>
      </div>

      <!-- Alternative 4: Getac F110-Ex -->
      <div class="alt-card">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-start justify-between gap-3 mb-3">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-[18px] font-semibold">4. Getac F110-Ex</h3>
            <p class="text-[13px]" style="color:var(--ash)">Best for: large-screen Windows in Zone 2</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1">
            <span class="badge badge-z2">Zone 2</span>
            <span class="badge badge-win">Windows</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-3 text-[13px] mb-4" style="color:var(--graphite)">
          <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">Display</strong><br/>11.6&Prime; IPS</div>
          <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">Weight</strong><br/>~1.4 kg</div>
          <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">Price</strong><br/>~&euro;3,800</div>
          <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">IP</strong><br/>IP66</div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-[14px] leading-relaxed mb-3" style="color:var(--graphite)">
          If your classified areas are Zone 2 only, the Getac F110-Ex offers the largest display (11.6&Prime;) and full Windows 11 at a lower price than the Aegex 10. Built on Getac&rsquo;s rugged F110 platform, it is MIL-STD-810H rated with excellent sunlight readability.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[14px] leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--graphite)">
          <strong style="color:var(--ink)">Trade-off:</strong> Zone 2 only &mdash; cannot enter Zone 1 areas. At 1.4 kg it is twice the weight of the Tab-Ex 03, so it functions more as a portable workstation than a handheld field device.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Alternative 5: Zebra XPAD L10 IS -->
      <div class="alt-card">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-start justify-between gap-3 mb-3">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-[18px] font-semibold">5. Zebra XPAD L10 IS</h3>
            <p class="text-[13px]" style="color:var(--ash)">Best for: enterprise barcode &amp; scanning workflows</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1">
            <span class="badge badge-z2">Zone 2</span>
            <span class="badge badge-android">Android</span>
            <span class="badge badge-win">Windows</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-3 text-[13px] mb-4" style="color:var(--graphite)">
          <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">Display</strong><br/>10.1&Prime;</div>
          <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">Weight</strong><br/>~1.1 kg</div>
          <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">Price</strong><br/>~&euro;3,500</div>
          <div><strong style="color:var(--ink)">IP</strong><br/>IP65</div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-[14px] leading-relaxed mb-3" style="color:var(--graphite)">
          Available in both Android and Windows configurations. The main draw is Zebra&rsquo;s enterprise barcode scanning ecosystem &mdash; if your warehouse or plant uses Zebra scanners, printers, and MDM (StageNow / VisibilityIQ), the XPAD L10 integrates seamlessly.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[14px] leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--graphite)">
          <strong style="color:var(--ink)">Trade-off:</strong> Zone 2 only, heavier, and lower IP rating. Less refined as a hazardous-area device compared to the purpose-built Zone 1 options above. Best suited for logistics and warehousing in Zone 2 classified areas.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Summary table -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="serif text-[28px] mb-6">Quick Comparison Table</h2>
      <div class="card p-0 overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-[13px]">
          <thead>
            <tr style="border-bottom:2px solid rgba(0,0,0,.08)">
              <th class="py-3 px-4 text-left font-medium" style="color:var(--graphite)">Tablet</th>
              <th class="py-3 px-4 text-left">Zone</th>
              <th class="py-3 px-4 text-left">OS</th>
              <th class="py-3 px-4 text-left">Display</th>
              <th class="py-3 px-4 text-left">Weight</th>
              <th class="py-3 px-4 text-left">Price</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(0,0,0,.06);background:rgba(37,99,235,.04)"><td class="py-3 px-4 font-semibold">ecom Tab-Ex 03 DZ2</td><td class="py-3 px-4">Zone 1</td><td class="py-3 px-4">Android 13</td><td class="py-3 px-4">10.1&Prime;</td><td class="py-3 px-4">690 g</td><td class="py-3 px-4">~&euro;3,200</td></tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(0,0,0,.06)"><td class="py-3 px-4">i.safe IS930.1</td><td class="py-3 px-4">Zone 1</td><td class="py-3 px-4">Android 12</td><td class="py-3 px-4">8.0&Prime;</td><td class="py-3 px-4">570 g</td><td class="py-3 px-4">~&euro;2,400</td></tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(0,0,0,.06)"><td class="py-3 px-4">Tab-Ex Pro DZ2</td><td class="py-3 px-4">Zone 1</td><td class="py-3 px-4">Android 13</td><td class="py-3 px-4">10.1&Prime;</td><td class="py-3 px-4">750 g</td><td class="py-3 px-4">~&euro;3,800</td></tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(0,0,0,.06)"><td class="py-3 px-4">Aegex 10 IS</td><td class="py-3 px-4">Zone 1</td><td class="py-3 px-4">Windows</td><td class="py-3 px-4">10.1&Prime;</td><td class="py-3 px-4">850 g</td><td class="py-3 px-4">~&euro;4,500</td></tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(0,0,0,.06)"><td class="py-3 px-4">Getac F110-Ex</td><td class="py-3 px-4">Zone 2</td><td class="py-3 px-4">Windows</td><td class="py-3 px-4">11.6&Prime;</td><td class="py-3 px-4">1.4 kg</td><td class="py-3 px-4">~&euro;3,800</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="py-3 px-4">Zebra XPAD L10</td><td class="py-3 px-4">Zone 2</td><td class="py-3 px-4">Android/Win</td><td class="py-3 px-4">10.1&Prime;</td><td class="py-3 px-4">1.1 kg</td><td class="py-3 px-4">~&euro;3,500</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Bottom line -->
    <div class="card mb-10">
      <h3 class="serif text-[22px] mb-3">Bottom Line</h3>
      <p class="text-[15px] leading-relaxed mb-3" style="color:var(--graphite)">
        The ecom Tab-Ex 03 DZ2 remains the default choice for most Zone 1 deployments &mdash; it has the best balance of screen size, weight, certification breadth, and Samsung enterprise integration. But &ldquo;best for most&rdquo; does not mean &ldquo;best for all.&rdquo;
      </p>
      <p class="text-[15px] leading-relaxed mb-3" style="color:var(--graphite)">
        <strong style="color:var(--ink)">If price is the priority</strong>, the i.safe IS930.1 saves &euro;800/unit with a trade-off in screen size. <strong style="color:var(--ink)">If Windows is required</strong>, the Aegex 10 is the only Zone 1 option. <strong style="color:var(--ink)">If Zone 2 is sufficient</strong>, the Getac and Zebra options offer larger screens and enterprise ecosystems at competitive prices.
      </p>
      <p class="text-[15px]" style="color:var(--graphite)">
        For the full field: <a href="/best-atex-tablets-2026.html" style="color:var(--accent)" class="hover:underline">Best ATEX Tablets 2026 &rarr;</a>
      </p>
    </div>

