      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-[15px] mb-2">What are the best alternatives to the ecom Tab-Ex?</h3>
          <p class="text-[14px] leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--graphite)">The top alternatives are the i.safe MOBILE IS930.1 (compact, affordable), Aegex 10 IS (Windows), ecom Tab-Ex Pro DZ2 (premium upgrade), Getac F110-Ex (large Windows Zone 2), and Zebra XPAD L10 IS (enterprise scanning). All are ATEX or IECEx certified.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-[15px] mb-2">Is the ecom Tab-Ex the best ATEX tablet?</h3>
          <p class="text-[14px] leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--graphite)">For most Android-based Zone 1 deployments, yes. But &ldquo;best&rdquo; depends on your specific requirements: OS, form factor, budget, and zone classification all matter.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-[15px] mb-2">Can I use a Zone 2 tablet in Zone 1?</h3>
          <p class="text-[14px] leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--graphite)">No. A Zone 2 certified tablet cannot enter Zone 1 classified areas. The Getac F110-Ex and Zebra XPAD L10 are Zone 2 only. If any part of your facility is Zone 1, you need the Tab-Ex 03, IS930.1, or Aegex 10.</p>
